.TH SDL_AddHintCallback 3 "SDL 3.1.3" "Simple Directmedia Layer" "SDL3 FUNCTIONS"
.SH NAME
SDL_AddHintCallback \- Add a function to watch a particular hint\[char46]
.SH HEADER FILE
Defined in SDL3/SDL_hints\[char46]h

.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include \(dqSDL3/SDL.h\(dq
.PP
.BI "bool SDL_AddHintCallback(const char *name, SDL_HintCallback callback, void *userdata);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The callback function is called _during_ this function, to provide it an
initial value, and again each time the hint's value changes\[char46]

.SH FUNCTION PARAMETERS
.TP
.I name
the hint to watch\[char46]
.TP
.I callback
An 
.BR SDL_HintCallback
 function that will be called when the hint value changes\[char46]
.TP
.I userdata
a pointer to pass to the callback function\[char46]
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns true on success or false on failure; call

.BR SDL_GetError
() for more information\[char46]

.SH THREAD SAFETY
It is safe to call this function from any thread\[char46]

.SH AVAILABILITY
This function is available since SDL 3\[char46]0\[char46]0\[char46]

